Show HN: Stack-chan – Open-source companion robot easy to assemble and customize
text: Introducing Stack-chan, an open-source hardware robot designed with Fusion360 and Kicad that is easy to assemble and customize. With just 6 screws, you can easily put together the robot and add your own features using JavaScript with the Moddable SDK. Stack-chan is completely open-source and the design files, firmware and software are all available on GitHub repository (https://github.com/meganetaaan/stack-chan) . Give it a try and customize it to your needs. We'd love to see what you create and hear your feedback on this open-source project.

title: Ask HN: Would the internet be better if domain squatting was made illegal?
text: Seems like all domains that are either short or catchy are taken and nothing exists if I go to them. I'm curious what you all think. Should a policy be made to stop the bad behaviour? Would it make the internet better or would things stay the same? Sure, someone can always make a long domain name or use .whatever but it seems like the popular websites rarely ever follow that example.
